<p><b>Priority:</b><br/>
High</p>

<p><b>Status:</b><br/>
Open</p>

<p><b>Assigned To:</b><br/>
Alla Vorobei</p>

<p><b>Environment:</b></p>

<p>Chrome 131.0.6778.266, Edge 132.0.2957.115, Safari 20619.2.8.11.12, Firefox 134.0.1</p>

<p><b>Preconditions:</b></p>

<p>The Amazon homepage is loaded successfully.<br/>
The Developer Tools are opened.</p>

<p><b>Steps to Reproduce:</b></p>

<p>Open the Amazon homepage on a desktop browser.<br/>
Resize the browser window to different screen widths (e.g., 1024px, 768px, 320px).<br/>
Observe the layout behavior for widths narrower than 800px.</p>

<p><b>Expected Results:</b></p>

<p>The website layout adjusts seamlessly to different screen sizes.<br/>
All key elements (navigation menu, CTAs, product details) remain visible and functional.<br/>
No horizontal scrolling is required on any screen size.</p>

<p><b>Actual Results:</b></p>

<p>On screens with a width of less than 800px the layout is misaligned.<br/>
Horizontal scrolling is required.<br/>
The issue occurs in Chrome, Edge, and Safari but does not reproduce in Firefox.<br/>
The website is not fully responsive for smaller screen sizes.</p>

<p><b>Reproducibility:</b></p>

<p>_<b>Affected Browsers:</b> _Chrome, Edge, Safari.<br/>
<em><b>Not Affected:</b></em> Firefox.</p>
